positive crew atmosphere, calm, technical, but communication difficulty, egocentric, not willing to further education.\n\nCandidate D: takes responsibility seriously, problem solving, concentration, responds to unexpected, but hot temper, know-it-all, weak leadership, no reliability explicit.\n\nGiven long-distance flights, reliability and crew morale are crucial. C has explicit reliability and positive atmosphere, despite communication difficulty. B's nasty remarks could be severe. A's lack of reliability unknown. D's hot temper also severe.\n\nThus C seems best overall. So vote Candidate C.\n\nWe also ask about any reliability info for A and D.\n\nThus public message: summarize, ask questions, state provisional vote.\n\nNow produce final."}
